			article#box-js(style="border-left-color: #e74c3c;")
				h3: a(href="https://github.com/CapacitorSet/box-js") Box.js
				p.
					A tool for studying malware (droppers) written in JavaScript and JScript. It makes use of the Node.js sandbox and provides a dummy implementation of some key ActiveX components (XMLHTTP, ADODB.Stream and others). Used successfully by security researchers and malware analysis services (#[a(href="https://www.sekoia.fr/en/") Sekoia]), and included in Lenny Zeltser's #[a(href="https://remnux.org/") REMNux] and #[a(href="https://github.com/ArchStrike/ArchStrike") ArchStrike].
				i malware analysis, node.js
			article#rebridge(style="border-left-color: #ff9900;")
				h3: a(href="https://github.com/CapacitorSet/rebridge") Rebridge
				p.
					A completely transparent bridge between JavaScript and Redis, as a Node.js package (#[a(href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/rebridge") rebridge] on npm).
				i redis, node.js
